1
00:00:18,980 --> 00:00:24,420
♪It's a sordid story that you've made♪

2
00:00:26,700 --> 00:00:32,700
♪Up to fill my mind with doubts and pain♪

3
00:00:34,780 --> 00:00:40,220
♪Blood I shed, and tears I wept,
are you satisfied?♪

4
00:00:40,220 --> 00:00:42,540
♪Enjoying what's mine♪

5
00:00:42,540 --> 00:00:49,500
♪Have you found a way
to bury guilt and shame♪

6
00:00:50,540 --> 00:00:55,020
♪I'm coming back to life♪

7
00:00:55,020 --> 00:00:58,700
♪Through the seven gates of death♪

8
00:00:58,700 --> 00:01:02,820
♪I'm coming back survived♪

9
00:01:02,820 --> 00:01:06,580
♪Feeling great to see you fall♪

10
00:01:06,580 --> 00:01:10,820
♪I'm taking back what's mine♪

11
00:01:10,820 --> 00:01:15,340
♪Bringing horror to the battlefield♪

12
00:01:15,340 --> 00:01:19,060
♪Lay it to waste♪

13
00:01:19,060 --> 00:01:22,940
♪Til the day my kingdom is reclaimed♪

14
00:01:38,260 --> 00:01:42,540
=Her Blaze=

15
00:01:43,300 --> 00:01:45,820
=Episode 5=

16
00:01:49,280 --> 00:01:50,079
Everyone,

17
00:01:50,480 --> 00:01:51,599
the morning briefing

18
00:01:51,599 --> 00:01:52,760
is about to begin.

19
00:01:52,760 --> 00:01:54,640
(Lysen Group)

20
00:01:54,640 --> 00:01:55,480
You know,

21
00:01:55,480 --> 00:01:57,439
everything must go well today.

22
00:01:57,560 --> 00:01:58,359
Rao Yuci.

23
00:02:01,400 --> 00:02:03,319
Rao Yuci.

24
00:02:14,479 --> 00:02:15,639
Did you see it clearly?

25
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:17,719
This is your boyfriend,

26
00:02:18,039 --> 00:02:18,840
Bai Muran.

27
00:02:19,919 --> 00:02:21,120
The one next to him is me.

28
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:33,680
Yuci,

29
00:02:34,240 --> 00:02:35,599
meet your old acquaintance.

30
00:02:42,980 --> 00:02:46,980
(Bai Muran,
Lysen Group Investment Dept 1)

31
00:02:47,960 --> 00:02:48,879
Long time no see.

32
00:02:51,919 --> 00:02:53,199
It still feels this way.

33
00:02:58,800 --> 00:03:00,039
You've recovered quite well.

34
00:03:03,039 --> 00:03:04,680
Why are you looking for me?

35
00:03:05,879 --> 00:03:08,199
After all this time,
don't you have anything to say to me?

36
00:03:11,080 --> 00:03:11,879
Come on,

37
00:03:12,879 --> 00:03:13,960
tell me your plan.

38
00:03:15,159 --> 00:03:16,439
Why did you return to Lysen?

39
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,900
Do you want to take
Bai Liangliang and me down?

40
00:03:21,840 --> 00:03:23,159
You really are outstanding.

41
00:03:24,879 --> 00:03:27,439
If it weren't for you three years ago,
Chuxia wouldn't exist.

42
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:30,520
It was precisely
because you were so brilliant

43
00:03:30,520 --> 00:03:32,280
that I chose to be with you.

44
00:03:37,719 --> 00:03:38,919
You didn't really think

45
00:03:38,919 --> 00:03:40,319
that I actually liked you, did you?

46
00:03:43,000 --> 00:03:43,879
How could I possibly

47
00:03:43,879 --> 00:03:45,400
like a lunatic?

48
00:04:04,599 --> 00:04:05,800
Our great genius

49
00:04:06,639 --> 00:04:08,120
is still emotionally unstable.

50
00:04:21,700 --> 00:04:23,100
(Xinkang Treatment Center-Rao Yuci
Psychiatric Treatment Records)

51
00:04:37,860 --> 00:04:39,260
(Xinkang Treatment Center
Medical Records)

52
00:04:39,260 --> 00:04:41,860
(Patient: Rao Yuci.
Department: Psychiatry)

53
00:04:43,260 --> 00:04:46,380
(Rao Yuci: Acute and Transient
Psychotic Disorder)

54
00:04:46,380 --> 00:04:47,540
(Janniel: That genius from Dept 3
actually came from a mental hospital.)

55
00:04:47,540 --> 00:04:48,820
(David from Investment Dept 2: ????????)

56
00:04:48,820 --> 00:04:50,060
(Kiki: Is that for real?)

57
00:04:50,060 --> 00:04:51,060
(Wayde: Even
the medical records were leaked.)

58
00:04:51,060 --> 00:04:51,780
(Qiao Lan: That's impossible.)

59
00:04:51,780 --> 00:04:52,780
(Zhou Ming: Xinkang Treatment Center?
Is that a mental asylum?)

60
00:04:52,780 --> 00:04:53,180
(Kavien: Our company
even hires lunatics now.)

61
00:04:53,180 --> 00:04:54,700
(Wan from Investment Dept 1:
How scary. Are we in danger?)

62
00:04:54,700 --> 00:04:55,860
(Ke: @HR Is this really okay?)

63
00:04:55,860 --> 00:04:56,940
(Annie: Let her go, otherwise...)

64
00:04:56,940 --> 00:04:58,300
(Fang Ping: Seems you
can't be a genius with a normal brain.)

65
00:04:58,300 --> 00:04:59,780
(Allan: @Dept 3,
you guys had better be careful.)

66
00:04:59,780 --> 00:05:01,020
(Andy: No wonder she's so antisocial.)

67
00:05:01,020 --> 00:05:02,420
(Zhang Haofeng from Dept 1: I greeted
her last time, and she ignored me.)

68
00:05:02,460 --> 00:05:03,300
(Wei from Investment Dept 2: Me too!!!)

69
00:05:03,300 --> 00:05:04,180
(Jason: Don't they do
background checks before hiring?)

70
00:05:04,180 --> 00:05:05,220
(Zhang Qi from Data Dept:
How did such private info get leaked?)

71
00:05:05,220 --> 00:05:05,820
(Momo: Everyone's a bit crazy
these days. Let it go.)

72
00:05:05,820 --> 00:05:06,700
(Sherman: A nutcase in Lysen?
She must be well-connected.)

73
00:05:06,700 --> 00:05:08,180
(Thomas: Mr. Jiang
recruited her personally.)

74
00:05:08,180 --> 00:05:09,500
(Thomas: I heard
he thinks very highly of her.)

75
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:11,839
Ms. Chen,

76
00:05:11,959 --> 00:05:12,879
have you seen it?

77
00:05:13,680 --> 00:05:14,879
That genius from Dept 3

78
00:05:15,040 --> 00:05:16,160
is actually a lunatic.

79
00:05:20,100 --> 00:05:22,839
(Patient Medical Records: Rao Yuci.
Acute and Transient Psychotic Disorder.)

80
00:05:22,839 --> 00:05:24,079
No way.

81
00:05:24,600 --> 00:05:25,319
How could she

82
00:05:25,319 --> 00:05:26,800
have come from such a place?

83
00:05:29,199 --> 00:05:30,390
What's wrong with this place?

84
00:05:31,600 --> 00:05:32,560
You're prejudiced.

85
00:05:33,160 --> 00:05:34,680
Haven't you heard the saying?

86
00:05:34,820 --> 00:05:35,600
Genius and madness

87
00:05:35,600 --> 00:05:36,839
are separated by a thin line.

88
00:05:45,560 --> 00:05:47,439
Rumors are spreading
through the company.

89
00:05:47,959 --> 00:05:48,680
They say

90
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:50,160
you stayed in a psychotherapy center

91
00:05:50,160 --> 00:05:51,120
for a long time.

92
00:05:53,120 --> 00:05:54,759
You could ask more directly.

93
00:05:55,550 --> 00:05:57,319
Is it because someone thinks
I'm dangerous?

94
00:05:57,319 --> 00:05:58,519
Then, I'll ask directly.

95
00:05:58,519 --> 00:05:59,399
Are you dangerous?

96
00:05:59,399 --> 00:06:00,839
Then, who do you think isn't?

97
00:06:02,879 --> 00:06:03,879
That's true.

98
00:06:05,920 --> 00:06:06,720
Back then,

99
00:06:06,959 --> 00:06:08,439
you were about to become

100
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:10,279
the head of Investment Dept 1.

101
00:06:10,959 --> 00:06:12,639
But you were immediately reported.

102
00:06:12,920 --> 00:06:13,720
Mr. Yu,

103
00:06:14,120 --> 00:06:15,120
do you really think

104
00:06:15,560 --> 00:06:16,839
that was just a coincidence?

105
00:06:20,110 --> 00:06:21,920
You've done
a very thorough background check.

106
00:06:23,000 --> 00:06:24,500
You must have put in a lot of effort.

107
00:06:25,800 --> 00:06:27,199
The effort was necessary.

108
00:06:27,800 --> 00:06:28,560
I just hope

109
00:06:28,560 --> 00:06:29,759
you understand

110
00:06:30,319 --> 00:06:31,160
who is a friend

111
00:06:31,879 --> 00:06:32,839
and who is an enemy.

112
00:06:33,680 --> 00:06:35,319
I also hope you understand

113
00:06:35,839 --> 00:06:37,639
there are no true friends in Lysen.

114
00:06:38,959 --> 00:06:40,480
Do you think I can't see

115
00:06:40,480 --> 00:06:41,759
that the matter

116
00:06:43,279 --> 00:06:44,560
was Bai Liangliang's doing?

117
00:06:46,890 --> 00:06:47,920
You went to great lengths

118
00:06:47,920 --> 00:06:49,600
to leak her medical records
to the whole company.

119
00:06:49,600 --> 00:06:50,720
By provoking her like this,

120
00:06:50,720 --> 00:06:51,839
what are you after?

121
00:06:54,360 --> 00:06:55,319
Only by provoking her

122
00:06:55,820 --> 00:06:57,720
can she act just like
she did three years ago.

123
00:06:59,319 --> 00:07:00,120
What do you mean?

124
00:07:01,959 --> 00:07:02,920
Provoke her,

125
00:07:03,399 --> 00:07:05,240
and she'll rush to implement her plan.

126
00:07:08,279 --> 00:07:09,079
Rao Yuci,

127
00:07:11,040 --> 00:07:12,279
I don't care who you are.

128
00:07:13,399 --> 00:07:14,279
I don't care

129
00:07:14,279 --> 00:07:15,319
why you came to Lysen.

130
00:07:16,120 --> 00:07:16,759
And I don't care

131
00:07:16,759 --> 00:07:18,160
how great your ambition is.

132
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:21,120
I just want to tell you

133
00:07:22,399 --> 00:07:23,800
that I have zero interest

134
00:07:23,800 --> 00:07:25,639
in those underhanded factional struggles.

135
00:07:25,639 --> 00:07:27,040
Besides,

136
00:07:27,040 --> 00:07:28,519
I have no leverage for you to use.

137
00:07:30,959 --> 00:07:32,199
My bottom line in Lysen...

138
00:07:32,199 --> 00:07:33,399
Your bottom line is to protect

139
00:07:33,399 --> 00:07:35,480
the hard-earned money
of countless Lysen investors.

140
00:07:35,480 --> 00:07:36,519
Am I right?

141
00:07:37,959 --> 00:07:39,319
Then, we aren't enemies.

142
00:07:41,000 --> 00:07:41,639
Rao Yuci,

143
00:07:41,639 --> 00:07:43,319
what exactly are you trying to do?

144
00:07:50,680 --> 00:07:51,480
Hello?

145
00:07:51,680 --> 00:07:52,480
It's me.

146
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:53,759
Rao Yuci's phone is off.

147
00:07:53,759 --> 00:07:54,720
She's with you, right?

148
00:07:55,439 --> 00:07:56,560
I know your rules.

149
00:07:56,759 --> 00:07:57,560
She is.

150
00:08:00,120 --> 00:08:00,879
Hello?

151
00:08:00,879 --> 00:08:01,600
Rao Yuci,

152
00:08:01,600 --> 00:08:02,480
it's Ren Jing.

153
00:08:02,500 --> 00:08:04,759
(HR Department)

154
00:08:04,759 --> 00:08:06,199
We have no intention of judging

155
00:08:06,199 --> 00:08:07,120
an employee's past.

156
00:08:08,120 --> 00:08:08,920
However, as the head

157
00:08:08,920 --> 00:08:10,160
of the HR department,

158
00:08:10,560 --> 00:08:11,240
I need to conduct

159
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:12,510
some investigations on our staff.

160
00:08:12,920 --> 00:08:13,720
I think

161
00:08:13,879 --> 00:08:15,120
you understand what I mean.

162
00:08:16,079 --> 00:08:17,000
Of course I do.

163
00:08:17,480 --> 00:08:18,279
So,

164
00:08:20,399 --> 00:08:22,240
you stayed in a mental treatment center

165
00:08:22,920 --> 00:08:24,079
for three years, correct?

166
00:08:24,519 --> 00:08:25,319
Yes.

167
00:08:25,959 --> 00:08:27,040
Then I'll be blunt.

168
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:30,399
Some of the company's upper management
are very troubled

169
00:08:30,399 --> 00:08:31,360
by your mental state.

170
00:08:33,120 --> 00:08:33,919
Upper management?

171
00:08:35,600 --> 00:08:36,559
Bai Liangliang?

172
00:08:37,000 --> 00:08:38,480
I'm sorry, I'm not at liberty to say.

173
00:08:38,480 --> 00:08:39,279
Then my mental state

174
00:08:39,279 --> 00:08:40,519
is also my personal privacy.

175
00:08:40,519 --> 00:08:42,170
Is it convenient
for you to disclose that?

176
00:08:46,360 --> 00:08:47,159
Miss Rao,

177
00:08:47,519 --> 00:08:48,399
I still remember

178
00:08:48,559 --> 00:08:50,159
your first day at Lysen.

179
00:08:50,320 --> 00:08:51,240
I made quite a scene

180
00:08:51,240 --> 00:08:53,200
bringing people
to the lobby to welcome you.

181
00:08:53,600 --> 00:08:55,360
Unexpectedly, you
went straight to the garage

182
00:08:55,360 --> 00:08:56,559
to meet Mr. Jiang.

183
00:08:57,360 --> 00:08:58,440
From that day on,

184
00:08:58,639 --> 00:09:00,159
I knew you were someone

185
00:09:00,240 --> 00:09:01,840
who doesn't play by the rules.

186
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:02,799
I apologize.

187
00:09:03,720 --> 00:09:04,440
As

188
00:09:04,440 --> 00:09:05,879
the HR Director,

189
00:09:06,039 --> 00:09:07,470
I am accountable to the shareholders,

190
00:09:07,480 --> 00:09:08,840
and even more so, for the safety

191
00:09:08,840 --> 00:09:09,559
of Lysen.

192
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,639
Of course,

193
00:09:10,879 --> 00:09:12,120
I shouldn't speculate

194
00:09:12,120 --> 00:09:13,240
on your personal condition.

195
00:09:13,519 --> 00:09:14,399
But we hope

196
00:09:14,399 --> 00:09:15,720
to have some professionals

197
00:09:15,720 --> 00:09:16,960
make a judgment.

198
00:09:17,559 --> 00:09:18,360
One moment.

199
00:09:27,080 --> 00:09:27,879
Dr. Chen.

200
00:09:45,320 --> 00:09:47,039
This is Dr. Chen.

201
00:09:47,799 --> 00:09:49,039
I hope you can cooperate.

202
00:09:49,450 --> 00:09:50,480
I'll leave it to you then.

203
00:09:53,759 --> 00:09:54,639
Let's begin.

204
00:09:57,919 --> 00:09:59,519
Rao Yuci, Rao Yuci!

205
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:00,879
Didn't we say we'd talk?

206
00:10:00,879 --> 00:10:01,679
Why are you running?

207
00:10:01,810 --> 00:10:02,919
Can you stop following me?

208
00:10:02,919 --> 00:10:03,639
No.

209
00:10:04,799 --> 00:10:06,480
Give me one reason not to let you go.

210
00:10:07,840 --> 00:10:09,039
You suddenly disappeared.

211
00:10:09,039 --> 00:10:10,519
Shouldn't I contact other people?

212
00:10:10,759 --> 00:10:12,480
I've already told you.

213
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:14,679
My job is tracking, following up,
and recording.

214
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:15,559
Can't you show some

215
00:10:15,559 --> 00:10:16,600
respect for my work?

216
00:10:18,000 --> 00:10:18,679
Let me ask you.

217
00:10:18,679 --> 00:10:19,480
How do you judge

218
00:10:19,480 --> 00:10:20,639
if a person is normal or not?

219
00:10:21,360 --> 00:10:22,399
Is anger abnormal?

220
00:10:22,399 --> 00:10:23,559
Is disappointment abnormal?

221
00:10:23,560 --> 00:10:25,360
If I hadn't recovered,
then what was the point

222
00:10:25,360 --> 00:10:27,290
of the psychological tests
I did before my discharge?

223
00:10:27,960 --> 00:10:28,759
Chen Mo,

224
00:10:29,159 --> 00:10:30,360
don't you want to ask yourself

225
00:10:30,879 --> 00:10:31,840
if you're normal?

226
00:10:42,799 --> 00:10:43,600
Rao Yuci.

227
00:10:47,159 --> 00:10:47,960
Rao Yuci!

228
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,879
I'm so worried about her.

229
00:10:55,200 --> 00:10:56,559
I want her to come home.

230
00:10:57,559 --> 00:10:59,480
Do you think she'll go back with me?

231
00:11:02,559 --> 00:11:03,720
It's time to leave work.

232
00:11:12,240 --> 00:11:13,039
Yuci.

233
00:11:14,799 --> 00:11:15,600
Yuci.

234
00:11:16,080 --> 00:11:18,039
Why are you hiding from me?

235
00:11:34,480 --> 00:11:35,279
Yuci.

236
00:11:35,759 --> 00:11:37,519
Why are you hiding from me?

237
00:11:38,519 --> 00:11:39,320
Yuci,

238
00:11:39,840 --> 00:11:41,200
come home with me,

239
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:42,000
okay?

240
00:11:43,000 --> 00:11:44,159
I miss you.

241
00:11:49,279 --> 00:11:50,879
Yuci, listen to me.

242
00:11:51,039 --> 00:11:51,879
Listen to me.

243
00:11:52,360 --> 00:11:53,639
I will definitely help you

244
00:11:53,639 --> 00:11:55,120
take good care of your parents.

245
00:11:56,279 --> 00:11:57,360
Come home with me.

246
00:11:57,600 --> 00:11:58,639
I'm your mother!

247
00:11:58,639 --> 00:12:00,240
Stop following me, I beg you!

248
00:12:00,279 --> 00:12:01,279
I'm begging you!

249
00:12:02,960 --> 00:12:03,759
Yuci!

250
00:12:03,759 --> 00:12:04,519
Ma'am.

251
00:12:04,840 --> 00:12:05,360
Yuci!

252
00:12:05,360 --> 00:12:06,120
Ma'am!

253
00:12:07,639 --> 00:12:08,840
Ma'am, stop chasing her.

254
00:12:09,519 --> 00:12:11,200
Her condition is still unstable.

255
00:12:11,250 --> 00:12:12,559
I'm afraid that if you push her,

256
00:12:12,559 --> 00:12:13,799
it will trigger her even more.

257
00:12:14,759 --> 00:12:15,679
Was it me?

258
00:12:17,039 --> 00:12:19,279
Was it because
I was too impulsive just now?

259
00:12:19,279 --> 00:12:20,840
I scared her.

260
00:12:21,279 --> 00:12:23,080
I scared her just now.

261
00:12:23,799 --> 00:12:26,159
Did... did I scare her?

262
00:12:26,159 --> 00:12:27,559
It's okay.

263
00:12:29,759 --> 00:12:31,360
I just want her to come home.

264
00:12:32,840 --> 00:12:35,200
Was it because I scared her?

265
00:12:35,360 --> 00:12:36,399
It's all right.

266
00:12:53,559 --> 00:12:54,360
Ma'am.

267
00:13:09,840 --> 00:13:10,639
Yuci.

268
00:13:12,279 --> 00:13:13,279
It's me.

269
00:13:17,200 --> 00:13:18,000
Mom...

270
00:13:20,559 --> 00:13:21,360
Yuci.

271
00:13:23,919 --> 00:13:24,759
Mom...

272
00:13:33,279 --> 00:13:34,240
Wait, baby.

273
00:13:34,240 --> 00:13:35,240
Your shoelace is untied.

274
00:13:36,759 --> 00:13:37,759
Look at you,

275
00:13:37,759 --> 00:13:39,279
running until you're all sweaty.

276
00:13:40,279 --> 00:13:41,519
Come, have some water.

277
00:13:42,879 --> 00:13:43,399
Look,

278
00:13:43,399 --> 00:13:45,080
your favorite little bunny cup.

279
00:13:46,070 --> 00:13:47,240
See? Your shoelace is untied.

280
00:13:47,240 --> 00:13:48,519
It's hard to walk like that.

281
00:13:49,120 --> 00:13:50,559
Let me tie it for you.

282
00:13:50,679 --> 00:13:51,519
My baby

283
00:13:51,519 --> 00:13:53,639
is the most well-behaved baby.

284
00:13:54,679 --> 00:13:55,480
Yuci,

285
00:13:55,879 --> 00:13:57,639
shoelaces must be tied well.

286
00:13:58,279 --> 00:14:00,159
They need to be tied neatly

287
00:14:00,159 --> 00:14:01,039
to look pretty.

288
00:14:01,039 --> 00:14:02,360
I know, Mom.

289
00:14:02,360 --> 00:14:03,080
Good girl.

290
00:14:36,450 --> 00:14:37,799
Aren't you tired of following me?

291
00:14:39,320 --> 00:14:40,360
I told you,

292
00:14:41,080 --> 00:14:42,720
after leaving the treatment center,

293
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,919
accepting others is your first lesson.

294
00:14:45,880 --> 00:14:46,799
Your family and friends

295
00:14:46,799 --> 00:14:48,000
are not your enemies.

296
00:14:48,799 --> 00:14:50,639
But what if the ones who hurt me
were them?

297
00:14:53,039 --> 00:14:54,679
If everyone in the world
abandoned you,

298
00:14:54,679 --> 00:14:56,639
could you still say that so lightly?

299
00:14:58,720 --> 00:14:59,519
Three years.

300
00:15:00,440 --> 00:15:01,639
I used all my pain

301
00:15:01,639 --> 00:15:03,039
waiting for one moment

302
00:15:03,679 --> 00:15:05,360
to demand an answer from this world.

303
00:15:06,830 --> 00:15:08,120
It's not like I can just let go

304
00:15:08,120 --> 00:15:10,470
because you followed me a few times
and told me to do so.

305
00:15:11,360 --> 00:15:12,320
This is my only

306
00:15:12,320 --> 00:15:13,320
reason for living.

307
00:15:16,399 --> 00:15:17,360
Listen here.

308
00:15:18,399 --> 00:15:20,279
When someone
who was once mired in darkness

309
00:15:21,159 --> 00:15:22,519
steps back into the light,

310
00:15:25,240 --> 00:15:28,320
she doesn't want
reconciliation or forgiveness.

311
00:15:33,120 --> 00:15:34,320
She wants justice.

312
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,559
(Bai Muran.)

313
00:15:46,159 --> 00:15:46,960
(Three years.)

314
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:49,519
(1095 days.)

315
00:15:50,879 --> 00:15:52,600
(Those memories turned into a blade,)

316
00:15:53,879 --> 00:15:55,519
(stabbing at me from the darkness.)

317
00:15:56,799 --> 00:15:57,879
(Every single moment,)

318
00:15:58,500 --> 00:16:00,240
(I've been rehearsing
the day I'd meet you)

319
00:16:00,240 --> 00:16:02,120
(inside my own mind.)

320
00:16:03,279 --> 00:16:05,799
(I thought I could look at your face
very calmly.)

321
00:16:06,840 --> 00:16:08,159
(But when I saw you that day,)

322
00:16:09,000 --> 00:16:10,799
(I still couldn't stop trembling.)

323
00:16:11,639 --> 00:16:13,039
(But it wasn't dread,)

324
00:16:13,799 --> 00:16:14,960
(nor was it fear.)

325
00:16:15,760 --> 00:16:17,240
(It was the resentment and excitement)

326
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:18,200
(clawing their way out)

327
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:19,360
(from every inch of skin
and every moment of pain)

328
00:16:19,360 --> 00:16:22,120
(during these three years.)

329
00:16:22,919 --> 00:16:25,279
(In a desperate situation,
who can truly be calm?)

330
00:16:25,960 --> 00:16:27,639
(You need a madman)

331
00:16:27,720 --> 00:16:29,120
(to stand in this story)

332
00:16:29,120 --> 00:16:31,039
(and tell you in your own way)

333
00:16:31,759 --> 00:16:32,799
(that for this story,)

334
00:16:33,360 --> 00:16:34,960
(nothing was ever predestined.)

335
00:16:40,039 --> 00:16:41,440
I found this on her computer.

336
00:16:41,919 --> 00:16:43,360
(In Transit)
It's being delivered tomorrow.

337
00:16:43,799 --> 00:16:45,200
Ms. Bai, you'd better be careful.

338
00:16:46,720 --> 00:16:47,440
How do you know

339
00:16:47,440 --> 00:16:49,120
she's not using it to cut fruit?

340
00:16:50,880 --> 00:16:51,919
If it were just for fruit,

341
00:16:51,919 --> 00:16:53,720
why would she look at it
whenever she's free?

342
00:16:54,200 --> 00:16:55,399
Besides, lately,

343
00:16:55,399 --> 00:16:56,879
the conversations between Rao Yuci

344
00:16:56,879 --> 00:16:58,639
and Mr. Yu have all been about you.

345
00:17:02,960 --> 00:17:04,079
The reason I'm reminding you

346
00:17:04,960 --> 00:17:05,880
is that I understand

347
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:07,880
you're the only big tree in this company

348
00:17:07,880 --> 00:17:09,240
that I can truly

349
00:17:09,240 --> 00:17:10,200
rely on.

350
00:17:12,079 --> 00:17:13,240
Thanks for the heads-up.

351
00:17:14,359 --> 00:17:15,680
I'm a grateful person.

352
00:17:16,079 --> 00:17:17,240
If you have any requests,

353
00:17:17,279 --> 00:17:18,480
just go ahead and state them.

354
00:17:21,319 --> 00:17:22,680
I want to join Investment Dept 1.

355
00:17:45,400 --> 00:17:47,520
People in the company
don't know about your past yet.

356
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:49,319
Shouldn't you be thanking me?

357
00:17:50,279 --> 00:17:51,599
Are you threatening me?

358
00:17:53,799 --> 00:17:55,680
How could this be a threat?

359
00:17:59,079 --> 00:18:00,519
I'm reminding you.

360
00:18:01,079 --> 00:18:02,400
As long as you keep me satisfied,

361
00:18:02,799 --> 00:18:03,839
you can still rely on me,

362
00:18:03,839 --> 00:18:05,119
this big tree.

363
00:18:14,799 --> 00:18:15,839
I'm not afraid of you.

364
00:18:16,920 --> 00:18:18,359
And I'm not afraid of you telling

365
00:18:18,359 --> 00:18:19,599
the whole company about this.

366
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,480
But if you do that,

367
00:18:21,759 --> 00:18:23,279
I will definitely get a lawyer.

368
00:18:24,519 --> 00:18:25,640
I will sue you.

369
00:18:25,759 --> 00:18:27,759
I'll sue Lysen until everyone knows!

370
00:18:30,079 --> 00:18:31,519
According to the law,

371
00:18:32,200 --> 00:18:33,720
if I sue Lysen,

372
00:18:34,680 --> 00:18:35,960
the summons will be sent directly

373
00:18:35,960 --> 00:18:37,119
to the legal representative.

374
00:18:37,559 --> 00:18:38,720
That person isn't you,

375
00:18:38,960 --> 00:18:40,400
nor is it Mr. Jiang.

376
00:18:40,400 --> 00:18:42,039
It's Mr. Li Wancheng.

377
00:18:44,480 --> 00:18:45,640
If you want to make a scene,

378
00:18:46,039 --> 00:18:47,000
so can I.

379
00:18:47,640 --> 00:18:49,240
You are the bad guys.

380
00:18:50,000 --> 00:18:51,880
You should be the ones afraid of me.

381
00:18:59,420 --> 00:19:01,559
Did you see the mass email
sent to the whole company?

382
00:19:01,559 --> 00:19:02,440
I saw it.

383
00:19:02,559 --> 00:19:04,690
I didn't expect her
to have been in a place like that.

384
00:19:04,799 --> 00:19:05,640
Oh my God.

385
00:19:06,039 --> 00:19:06,839
Look at her.

386
00:19:21,480 --> 00:19:22,279
Yuci.

387
00:19:27,000 --> 00:19:28,000
Now that my medical records

388
00:19:28,000 --> 00:19:29,470
are being circulated
throughout the company,

389
00:19:30,480 --> 00:19:31,559
aren't you afraid of me?

390
00:19:34,920 --> 00:19:35,880
I fear nothing now,

391
00:19:35,880 --> 00:19:36,680
Yuci.

392
00:19:37,119 --> 00:19:39,480
I'll just sit here.

393
00:19:39,480 --> 00:19:41,680
I was just in the restroom
and ran into Bai Liangliang.

394
00:19:41,880 --> 00:19:43,160
I even had a fight with her.

395
00:19:44,000 --> 00:19:45,160
I'm planning to resign.

396
00:19:49,319 --> 00:19:50,240
Why resign?

397
00:19:51,519 --> 00:19:53,559
After you resign,
will you go to another company

398
00:19:54,119 --> 00:19:55,799
and be a sacrificed prey again?

399
00:19:58,559 --> 00:19:59,480
Tell me,

400
00:19:59,480 --> 00:20:00,200
what kind of

401
00:20:00,200 --> 00:20:01,359
mental problem does she have?

402
00:20:03,160 --> 00:20:03,880
I heard

403
00:20:03,880 --> 00:20:06,319
she hurt someone three years ago.

404
00:20:06,960 --> 00:20:08,359
Really? That happened?

405
00:20:08,519 --> 00:20:09,440
No way.

406
00:20:09,880 --> 00:20:12,319
Having a psycho in the office
is really too much to handle.

407
00:20:14,880 --> 00:20:16,240
Who the heck? Didn't you see...

408
00:20:17,880 --> 00:20:18,920
Mr. Yu.

409
00:20:26,839 --> 00:20:27,720
Order a few more dishes

410
00:20:27,799 --> 00:20:28,759
and shut your mouths.

411
00:20:29,759 --> 00:20:30,559
Yes, sir.

412
00:20:35,839 --> 00:20:36,640
Manager.

413
00:20:41,799 --> 00:20:43,319
I was a bit impulsive just now, right?

414
00:20:44,799 --> 00:20:46,359
Everyone has impulsive moments.

415
00:20:46,400 --> 00:20:47,200
Right?

416
00:20:51,079 --> 00:20:53,160
Do you want to take a few days off

417
00:20:53,200 --> 00:20:54,079
to get some rest?

418
00:20:57,119 --> 00:20:58,000
You surely don't think

419
00:20:58,000 --> 00:20:59,160
I'm sick, do you?

420
00:21:01,279 --> 00:21:02,559
Then, why should I rest?

421
00:21:03,559 --> 00:21:05,079
I have so much work to finish.

422
00:21:07,119 --> 00:21:08,279
I'm done eating. I'm leaving.

423
00:21:31,319 --> 00:21:32,340
Close the door behind you.

424
00:21:34,799 --> 00:21:36,160
Let's just talk with the door open.

425
00:21:36,640 --> 00:21:38,279
Lest you think I'm dangerous too.

426
00:21:51,240 --> 00:21:53,759
What's with the two security guards
at our Dept 3 entrance?

427
00:21:55,599 --> 00:21:57,119
Did HR hire so many people

428
00:21:57,180 --> 00:21:58,279
that there's no space left?

429
00:21:58,700 --> 00:22:00,200
Or are they guarding against someone?

430
00:22:01,119 --> 00:22:02,640
It's not you anyway, so don't worry.

431
00:22:03,279 --> 00:22:04,400
You know me.

432
00:22:05,000 --> 00:22:06,480
I won't let anyone go

433
00:22:06,480 --> 00:22:07,559
who might harm Lysen,

434
00:22:08,960 --> 00:22:09,720
not even the people

435
00:22:09,720 --> 00:22:10,640
Mr. Jiang chose.

436
00:22:11,319 --> 00:22:13,660
That psychiatrist
was brought in by Bai Liangliang, right?

437
00:22:16,440 --> 00:22:17,559
So you're on the same side

438
00:22:17,559 --> 00:22:18,599
as Bai Liangliang now?

439
00:22:21,880 --> 00:22:23,160
I don't take sides.

440
00:22:23,599 --> 00:22:24,759
I only belong to Lysen.

441
00:22:34,519 --> 00:22:35,319
Ren Jing,

442
00:22:36,799 --> 00:22:38,279
I didn't come here to argue with you.

443
00:22:39,380 --> 00:22:41,039
Doesn't Bai Liangliang's method of dealing

444
00:22:41,039 --> 00:22:42,799
with Rao Yuci seem familiar to you?

445
00:22:43,319 --> 00:22:44,359
Sitting in your position,

446
00:22:44,359 --> 00:22:45,680
can't you see

447
00:22:45,680 --> 00:22:47,759
who the truly
dangerous person is in Lysen?

448
00:22:50,000 --> 00:22:51,119
I'm talking to you.

449
00:22:51,700 --> 00:22:53,480
How I got transferred
from Dept 1 to Dept 3,

450
00:22:53,480 --> 00:22:55,020
don't you know the truth in your heart?

451
00:22:55,030 --> 00:22:55,880
And between the two of us...

452
00:22:55,880 --> 00:22:56,880
Are you finished?

453
00:22:59,140 --> 00:23:00,440
If you're finished, please leave.

454
00:23:05,480 --> 00:23:06,920
What did Bai Liangliang give you?

455
00:23:08,900 --> 00:23:10,960
Please complete
the psychological self-assessment

456
00:23:10,960 --> 00:23:12,550
issued by the HR department
as soon as possible.

457
00:23:12,560 --> 00:23:14,370
I see you've been
under a lot of pressure lately.

458
00:23:14,600 --> 00:23:15,960
You have quite a lot of leave left.

459
00:23:16,559 --> 00:23:17,359
How about

460
00:23:17,559 --> 00:23:18,519
I help you take a break?

461
00:23:29,000 --> 00:23:29,799
Mr. Yu,

462
00:23:31,350 --> 00:23:32,880
please close the door on your way out.

463
00:23:42,240 --> 00:23:43,039
Childish.

464
00:23:44,580 --> 00:23:45,660
(Investment Dept 1)

465
00:23:46,279 --> 00:23:47,440
Fill this out carefully.

466
00:23:50,160 --> 00:23:52,400
Ms. Bai, this is the psychological
self-assessment form

467
00:23:52,400 --> 00:23:53,480
from the HR department.

468
00:23:53,500 --> 00:23:55,920
Director Ren even specially invited
a professional counselor

469
00:23:55,920 --> 00:23:57,640
to conduct stress tests for everyone.

470
00:23:58,400 --> 00:23:59,119
Understood.

471
00:23:59,119 --> 00:23:59,839
All right.

472
00:24:12,900 --> 00:24:14,980
(Lysen Group Employee
Well-being Self-Assessment Form)

473
00:24:19,400 --> 00:24:20,319
Hello, Ms. Ren.

474
00:24:21,039 --> 00:24:23,000
I've already received
the self-assessment forms.

475
00:24:23,250 --> 00:24:24,279
Pleasure working with you.

476
00:24:34,960 --> 00:24:35,759
Dr. Chen,

477
00:24:37,319 --> 00:24:39,640
these are the self-assessment forms
for all the staff.

478
00:24:42,720 --> 00:24:43,640
I hope you

479
00:24:44,090 --> 00:24:45,359
will evaluate them thoroughly.

480
00:24:48,839 --> 00:24:50,240
Hello, which one of you is Rao Yuci?

481
00:24:50,640 --> 00:24:51,440
I am.

482
00:24:51,519 --> 00:24:52,400
You have a delivery.

483
00:24:54,480 --> 00:24:55,279
Thank you.

484
00:25:15,140 --> 00:25:17,580
(Name: Rao Yuci
Department: Investment Dept 3)

485
00:25:28,799 --> 00:25:30,039
You said you know me.

486
00:25:30,359 --> 00:25:31,240
What keywords

487
00:25:31,240 --> 00:25:32,519
did you read in my files?

488
00:25:33,279 --> 00:25:34,160
Math genius?

489
00:25:34,160 --> 00:25:35,160
Dangerous and violent?

490
00:25:35,640 --> 00:25:37,519
A person once mired in darkness

491
00:25:38,400 --> 00:25:39,720
walks back into the light.

492
00:25:42,480 --> 00:25:45,559
What she wants
isn't reconciliation or forgiveness.

493
00:25:47,559 --> 00:25:48,759
What she wants is justice.

494
00:25:56,319 --> 00:25:57,119
Hello?

495
00:25:57,680 --> 00:25:58,640
Let's meet.

496
00:25:59,000 --> 00:26:00,790
Tonight, at the company's
observation deck.

497
00:26:01,880 --> 00:26:03,759
Fine. Be there or be square.

498
00:26:45,380 --> 00:26:46,400
It's beautiful, isn't it?

499
00:26:49,559 --> 00:26:51,160
Looking down from here,

500
00:26:52,160 --> 00:26:53,720
everything becomes insignificant.

501
00:26:54,680 --> 00:26:55,640
Take a good look.

502
00:26:56,880 --> 00:26:59,039
I'm afraid you won't have
another chance to come up.

503
00:27:09,920 --> 00:27:11,680
I'm starting to understand

504
00:27:11,680 --> 00:27:13,359
why your dad hates you so much.

505
00:27:14,200 --> 00:27:15,599
Between a genius and a freak,

506
00:27:15,799 --> 00:27:17,240
there's only a fine line.

507
00:27:18,359 --> 00:27:20,160
You really are too strange.

508
00:27:20,799 --> 00:27:22,400
Like a ghost,

509
00:27:22,960 --> 00:27:24,279
lingering and never leaving.

510
00:27:26,079 --> 00:27:28,279
Bai Liangliang, standing here,
aren't you afraid?

511
00:27:30,079 --> 00:27:30,880
At the summit,

512
00:27:30,880 --> 00:27:32,599
there's only room for one person.

513
00:27:32,960 --> 00:27:34,000
So between the two of us,

514
00:27:34,000 --> 00:27:35,440
one of us is bound

515
00:27:36,839 --> 00:27:37,960
to fall.

516
00:27:41,839 --> 00:27:42,960
It's been three years.

517
00:27:44,039 --> 00:27:45,759
Haven't you realized it yet?

518
00:27:46,000 --> 00:27:47,599
The root of everything

519
00:27:47,599 --> 00:27:49,680
is because of you, Rao Yuci.

520
00:27:50,119 --> 00:27:52,920
Thanks to someone like you
who is out of step with the world,

521
00:27:53,319 --> 00:27:55,559
I had the chance to climb up.

522
00:27:57,839 --> 00:27:58,759
Your parents

523
00:27:59,680 --> 00:28:01,319
don't even want to mention you.

524
00:28:02,160 --> 00:28:03,599
They prefer to believe

525
00:28:03,599 --> 00:28:05,000
that I am what their daughter

526
00:28:05,000 --> 00:28:06,279
should have been like.

527
00:28:07,319 --> 00:28:08,119
Rao Yuci,

528
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:10,119
living like this,

529
00:28:10,119 --> 00:28:11,720
don't you feel like a failure?

530
00:28:11,720 --> 00:28:12,480
Say that again.

531
00:28:12,480 --> 00:28:13,200
Rao Yuci!

532
00:28:14,079 --> 00:28:14,880
Stop it.

533
00:28:18,240 --> 00:28:19,039
Liangliang,

534
00:28:19,440 --> 00:28:20,279
are you okay?

535
00:28:20,759 --> 00:28:21,599
I'm okay.

536
00:28:22,240 --> 00:28:23,519
I don't know why

537
00:28:23,640 --> 00:28:24,960
she wanted to hurt me like this.

538
00:28:27,079 --> 00:28:28,440
I didn't hurt you.

539
00:28:29,920 --> 00:28:31,200
Ms. Ren, she's acting.

540
00:28:31,640 --> 00:28:32,720
I'm acting?

541
00:28:33,799 --> 00:28:35,000
She wanted to kill me.

542
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,200
There's a knife inside this box.

543
00:28:37,700 --> 00:28:39,279
Liangliang, what are you talking about?

544
00:28:39,960 --> 00:28:40,759
You were the one

545
00:28:40,759 --> 00:28:42,400
who told me to bring this box up, right?

546
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:09,440
We are friends.

547
00:29:10,799 --> 00:29:12,279
Her birthday is coming up,

548
00:29:12,799 --> 00:29:13,839
so she asked me to come up

549
00:29:14,119 --> 00:29:15,519
so we could chat.

550
00:29:16,200 --> 00:29:17,079
I don't know why

551
00:29:17,079 --> 00:29:18,559
she suddenly became like this.

552
00:29:19,319 --> 00:29:20,240
Impossible.

553
00:29:21,039 --> 00:29:22,920
There should be a knife inside this box.

554
00:29:23,400 --> 00:29:24,200
Where's the knife?

555
00:29:24,440 --> 00:29:25,240
Where's the knife?

556
00:29:25,400 --> 00:29:26,480
Let Rao Yuci go first.

557
00:29:29,660 --> 00:29:31,039
Liangliang, what's wrong with you?

558
00:29:33,559 --> 00:29:34,880
I even brought you

559
00:29:35,319 --> 00:29:36,759
the food you like most.

560
00:29:42,160 --> 00:29:43,799
Is it the most familiar taste?

561
00:29:44,720 --> 00:29:45,880
The taste of mother.

562
00:29:47,759 --> 00:29:48,759
Rao Yuci!

563
00:29:49,710 --> 00:29:50,440
Quickly, get her.

564
00:29:50,440 --> 00:29:51,559
You're acting!

565
00:29:52,079 --> 00:29:53,240
Shut up!

566
00:29:53,400 --> 00:29:54,759
You're the one acting!

567
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:56,559
You lunatic!

568
00:29:56,960 --> 00:29:58,400
Liangliang, calm down.

569
00:29:58,640 --> 00:29:59,440
Ms. Ren,

570
00:29:59,519 --> 00:30:01,160
Rao Yuci is a lunatic.

571
00:30:01,200 --> 00:30:02,160
She's acting.

572
00:30:02,160 --> 00:30:03,279
There must be a knife.

573
00:30:06,000 --> 00:30:06,799
Bai Liangliang,

574
00:30:07,359 --> 00:30:08,279
I saw it.

575
00:30:09,079 --> 00:30:10,119
And I've heard about it.

576
00:30:11,559 --> 00:30:12,480
But the doctor says

577
00:30:13,039 --> 00:30:14,680
Rao Yuci has been
recovering well lately.

578
00:30:15,799 --> 00:30:16,599
As for you,

579
00:30:17,240 --> 00:30:18,440
you need to calm down.

580
00:30:18,660 --> 00:30:20,780
There are some questions
I need to ask you properly.

581
00:30:25,039 --> 00:30:25,839
Dr. Chen,

582
00:30:26,880 --> 00:30:28,240
this is the assistant to Ms. Bai

583
00:30:28,240 --> 00:30:29,200
of Investment Dept 1.

584
00:30:29,480 --> 00:30:30,559
She has something to say.

585
00:30:31,400 --> 00:30:33,839
Ms. Bai seems to have been
in a bad mood lately.

586
00:30:35,119 --> 00:30:36,680
Has she had any unusual behavior?

587
00:30:44,039 --> 00:30:45,799
Ms. Bai ordered me to buy this.

588
00:30:46,440 --> 00:30:47,240
That day,

589
00:30:47,480 --> 00:30:49,880
she even gave the medicine
to Li Mingxuan from my department.

590
00:30:50,119 --> 00:30:50,920
These past few days,

591
00:30:51,400 --> 00:30:53,640
she's often been losing her temper
in the office alone,

592
00:30:53,680 --> 00:30:55,240
and she even smashed a vase.

593
00:31:00,680 --> 00:31:01,839
What I want to know is...

594
00:31:03,150 --> 00:31:04,160
Is there something wrong

595
00:31:04,880 --> 00:31:05,720
(Bai Liangliang, Investment Dept 1)
with this person?

596
00:31:22,740 --> 00:31:28,700
(History of medication use,
history of assault)

597
00:31:28,759 --> 00:31:30,200
You think I'm crazy?

598
00:31:31,279 --> 00:31:32,839
No one thinks you're crazy.

599
00:31:34,200 --> 00:31:34,960
You might just

600
00:31:34,960 --> 00:31:36,200
be a bit emotional lately...

601
00:31:36,200 --> 00:31:37,440
I'm not emotional.

602
00:31:37,720 --> 00:31:39,079
All my emotions revolve around you.

603
00:31:39,280 --> 00:31:40,640
As long as you're in the company,

604
00:31:40,640 --> 00:31:41,799
I am in danger,

605
00:31:41,799 --> 00:31:43,200
and Lysen is in danger.

606
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:45,119
Liangliang, I have never once hurt you.

607
00:31:45,119 --> 00:31:46,680
Why do you keep treating me as an enemy?

608
00:31:46,680 --> 00:31:47,400
You're acting, you lunatic!

609
00:31:47,400 --> 00:31:48,720
Besides, we're friends.

610
00:31:48,720 --> 00:31:49,880
You're acting!

611
00:31:50,119 --> 00:31:51,000
Calm down.

612
00:31:53,240 --> 00:31:53,799
Ms. Ren,

613
00:31:53,799 --> 00:31:55,160
let us have a few words alone.

614
00:31:57,240 --> 00:31:58,039
Go.

615
00:32:14,519 --> 00:32:16,599
Rao Yuci, you're a devil.

616
00:32:21,880 --> 00:32:23,359
Liangliang, so are you.

617
00:32:26,359 --> 00:32:27,880
It wasn't convenient to speak earlier.

618
00:32:28,839 --> 00:32:30,279
I'll tell you now.

619
00:32:31,480 --> 00:32:32,359
That knife

620
00:32:32,759 --> 00:32:33,799
is still here.

621
00:32:35,279 --> 00:32:36,079
Only,

622
00:32:37,000 --> 00:32:38,759
it's not meant for you.

623
00:32:42,720 --> 00:32:43,680
Do you remember

624
00:32:43,680 --> 00:32:45,319
something you once told me?

625
00:32:46,839 --> 00:32:47,799
Everyone has

626
00:32:47,799 --> 00:32:49,079
a black dog in their heart.

627
00:32:50,599 --> 00:32:52,160
Now I want to ask you,

628
00:32:53,440 --> 00:32:55,119
what is that black dog

629
00:32:55,440 --> 00:32:56,319
in your heart?

630
00:32:57,480 --> 00:32:58,799
Do you even know?

631
00:33:13,260 --> 00:33:17,300
(Fifteen years ago)

632
00:33:20,119 --> 00:33:20,920
Xinyi,

633
00:33:21,319 --> 00:33:22,559
is this your home?

634
00:33:22,680 --> 00:33:23,480
Yeah.

635
00:33:23,680 --> 00:33:24,400
Come on,

636
00:33:24,400 --> 00:33:25,160
come home with me.

637
00:33:28,599 --> 00:33:29,480
Come on in, Liangliang.

638
00:33:29,799 --> 00:33:30,799
Welcome to my home.

639
00:33:32,440 --> 00:33:33,319
You're back.

640
00:33:33,759 --> 00:33:34,759
Are you tired?

641
00:33:36,240 --> 00:33:37,039
Mom,

642
00:33:37,319 --> 00:33:38,559
this is my good friend,

643
00:33:38,599 --> 00:33:39,400
Bai Liangliang.

644
00:33:39,559 --> 00:33:40,759
Xinyi always says

645
00:33:40,759 --> 00:33:42,599
Liangliang is the prettiest in class.

646
00:33:42,799 --> 00:33:44,359
I finally get to meet her today.

647
00:33:44,799 --> 00:33:45,599
Hello, ma'am.

648
00:33:46,640 --> 00:33:48,279
Mom, we're going upstairs now.

649
00:33:48,279 --> 00:33:49,400
Do you want any fruit?

650
00:33:49,400 --> 00:33:50,839
I'll cut some for you.

651
00:33:50,839 --> 00:33:51,480
Okay.

652
00:33:51,720 --> 00:33:52,519
Xinyi,

653
00:33:52,599 --> 00:33:54,279
your mom's perfume smells so good.

654
00:34:03,880 --> 00:34:05,039
What is that smell?

655
00:34:26,199 --> 00:34:27,199
Welcome back, Liang.

656
00:34:27,300 --> 00:34:28,119
Come on in quickly.

657
00:34:28,119 --> 00:34:29,239
Dinner's almost ready.

658
00:34:29,920 --> 00:34:31,280
The school needs an activity fee.

659
00:34:31,920 --> 00:34:32,800
One hundred yuan.

660
00:34:33,400 --> 00:34:34,400
Another fee?

661
00:34:35,360 --> 00:34:36,599
You haven't learned a thing,

662
00:34:36,599 --> 00:34:37,719
yet all we do is pay fees.

663
00:34:38,400 --> 00:34:39,960
The parent-teacher meeting is coming up.

664
00:34:39,960 --> 00:34:41,800
I really need to ask
your teacher about this.

665
00:34:42,079 --> 00:34:43,320
The meeting's over.

666
00:34:44,480 --> 00:34:46,239
You didn't have time,
so I didn't tell you.

667
00:35:23,079 --> 00:35:23,920
Come on, let's eat.

668
00:35:28,360 --> 00:35:29,800
Why are we having this again?

669
00:35:31,880 --> 00:35:33,320
We haven't had many customers.

670
00:35:33,400 --> 00:35:34,960
There's leftover duck. It'd be a waste.

671
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,679
Just make do with it.

672
00:35:43,719 --> 00:35:44,519
Li,

673
00:35:44,880 --> 00:35:45,719
see if you

674
00:35:45,719 --> 00:35:47,440
can help me with some money for now

675
00:35:47,519 --> 00:35:49,360
to pay the kid's fees?

676
00:35:50,700 --> 00:35:52,039
Where did you get those clothes?

677
00:35:53,599 --> 00:35:54,800
I'm talking to you.

678
00:35:59,450 --> 00:36:00,559
You have your own clothes,

679
00:36:00,559 --> 00:36:01,880
but you insist on
wearing someone else's?

680
00:36:01,880 --> 00:36:02,480
Vain!

681
00:36:02,480 --> 00:36:03,430
Who are you throwing things at?

682
00:36:03,440 --> 00:36:04,440
I provide your food and clothes,

683
00:36:04,440 --> 00:36:05,660
and this is how you turn out?

684
00:36:06,800 --> 00:36:07,519
How

685
00:36:07,519 --> 00:36:08,599
can you be so thoughtless?

686
00:36:08,599 --> 00:36:09,519
How could you wear

687
00:36:09,519 --> 00:36:10,760
a guest's clothes?

688
00:36:11,119 --> 00:36:12,039
When the guest arrives,

689
00:36:12,039 --> 00:36:13,639
how is your uncle supposed to explain?

690
00:36:13,639 --> 00:36:15,400
You're punished today.
No food for you.

691
00:36:15,400 --> 00:36:16,119
Go!

692
00:36:20,000 --> 00:36:20,840
This child...

693
00:36:20,840 --> 00:36:22,390
The older she gets,
the more thoughtless she is.

694
00:36:22,400 --> 00:36:23,199
Take this.

695
00:36:23,280 --> 00:36:24,920
Go out and get something good to eat.

696
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:29,760
I'm sorry.

697
00:36:30,760 --> 00:36:31,360
I'm sorry.

698
00:36:31,360 --> 00:36:32,440
You and your mother are the same.

699
00:36:32,440 --> 00:36:33,639
You are just like centipedes,

700
00:36:33,960 --> 00:36:35,360
crawling from one house to another.

701
00:36:37,679 --> 00:36:38,679
On behalf of the child,

702
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:40,599
I offer my apologies to you.

703
00:36:42,119 --> 00:36:42,920
I'm sorry.

704
00:37:12,840 --> 00:37:13,960
(Everyone has)

705
00:37:13,960 --> 00:37:15,480
(a black dog in their heart.)

706
00:37:16,159 --> 00:37:17,840
(It is the part of yourself)

707
00:37:17,840 --> 00:37:18,960
(that you dare not face.)

708
00:37:19,679 --> 00:37:22,159
(Once that black dog starts to roar,)

709
00:37:24,000 --> 00:37:24,920
(Bai Liangliang,)

710
00:37:25,559 --> 00:37:27,440
(you must wait for your moment)

711
00:37:28,000 --> 00:37:29,440
(so that even fear)

712
00:37:29,679 --> 00:37:31,159
(can be used by you.)

713
00:37:38,260 --> 00:37:41,700
=Episode 5=
(Old Dream)

714
00:37:42,501 --> 00:37:44,941
(All animals in this production
were treated humanely)

715
00:37:44,941 --> 00:37:51,141
♪Take a breath and swallow
the words you couldn't say♪

716
00:37:51,901 --> 00:37:55,101
♪No need to force your heart anymore♪

717
00:37:55,101 --> 00:37:59,621
♪Searching for the season
we once missed♪

718
00:37:59,621 --> 00:38:07,141
♪Leave this place,
though wounded still stay strong♪

719
00:38:07,141 --> 00:38:11,061
♪You must believe
one day the rain will fall♪

720
00:38:11,061 --> 00:38:15,101
♪And wash away the mud
that stains your soul♪

721
00:38:15,101 --> 00:38:18,621
♪Find your freedom in the wild♪

722
00:38:18,621 --> 00:38:22,581
♪Take your stride and move ahead♪

723
00:38:22,581 --> 00:38:26,741
♪I will stay behind
and wait for your eyes♪

724
00:38:26,741 --> 00:38:30,941
♪To rebuild
the same flesh and soul again♪

725
00:38:30,941 --> 00:38:34,741
♪Wander freely through the thorns♪

726
00:38:34,741 --> 00:38:38,821
♪Keep walking through the light♪

727
00:38:38,821 --> 00:38:43,021
♪Fate is absurd, don't stop for anyone♪

728
00:38:43,021 --> 00:38:49,341
♪What you dare to lose
will one day be your own♪

729
00:39:06,461 --> 00:39:13,101
♪I'm sorry, I still owe you these words♪

730
00:39:13,101 --> 00:39:16,941
♪An apology that came too late♪

731
00:39:16,941 --> 00:39:21,581
♪Yet it's also the path
that saves my soul♪

732
00:39:21,661 --> 00:39:29,061
♪When the cold wind
passes it takes the past away♪

733
00:39:29,061 --> 00:39:33,141
♪You must believe and stand unwavering♪

734
00:39:33,141 --> 00:39:37,221
♪There will be hands
to pull you from the deep♪

735
00:39:37,221 --> 00:39:41,221
♪Find your freedom in the silence♪

736
00:39:41,221 --> 00:39:44,981
♪Let your wounds be mended♪

737
00:39:44,981 --> 00:39:49,181
♪Gray is not the past
and pain is not a shame♪

738
00:39:49,181 --> 00:39:53,341
♪Sometimes the sunlight
makes the world look crueler♪

739
00:39:53,341 --> 00:39:57,061
♪Wander through the echoes of regret♪

740
00:39:57,061 --> 00:40:01,101
♪Be forgiven and be sheltered♪

741
00:40:01,101 --> 00:40:05,141
♪After everything shatters,
hold my hand♪

742
00:40:05,141 --> 00:40:11,341
♪A flower reborn
will finally bloom forever♪
